"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The seaborn documentation states that the rc argument in set_style() function can only override the parameters that are part of the style definition. However, 'grid.linewidth' is a matplotlib parameter that is not part of the style definition. It should be passed to the set_theme() function or set_context() should not be used for this purpose. Instead, use matplotlib's rcParams to set the grid linewidth.\",\n  \"patch\": \"5,8c5,8\\n< scale_dict = {\\n<     'grid.linewidth': 4\\n< }\\n< sns.set_context(rc=scale_dict)\\n---\\n> import matplotlib as mpl\\n> mpl.rcParams['grid.linewidth'] = 4\\n> sns.set_context()\\n\"\n}"